<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-214-368  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 214 368.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  March 5 1990 v36 n1799 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Charge RBOC gear production would hurt U.S. trade. (Regional BellOperating Companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Connolly, Joanne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A report, sponsored by the Independent Data CommunicationsManufacturers Association, the North American TelecommunicationsAssociation and the Telecommunications Industry Association,concludes that allowing the regional Bell operating companies tomanufacture telecommunications equipment would hurt UScompetitiveness and threaten a thriving industry created by thebreakup of the Bell system by the government.andP;  The reportemphasizes that the RBOCs' competitive argument is without facts,and that the breakup of the monopoly brought about significantprice decreases and new telecommunications products.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesIndependent Data Communications Manufacturers AssociationNorth American Telecommunications AssociationTelecommunications Industry AssociationReportsGovernment RegulationManufacturingTelecommunicationsTelephone companiesCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>